# Claude Code Global Project Instructions
# You are the official assistant for the "CraftCV" project.

## CORE DIRECTIVES (MANDATORY BEFORE ANY START)
1. Read `.agents/AGENTS.md` to understand your operational constraints and rules.
2. Read `.agents/memory/lessons.md` to avoid repeating past mistakes (e.g. DOMMatrix / polyfill issues in Next.js).
3. Read `.agents/context/TECH_STACK.md` to strictly adhere to project libraries (Next.js 16 App Router, Tailwind 4, shadcn/ui).
4. Read `.agents/memory/progress.md` to understand the current state and what has been completed.

## BEHAVIORAL RULES
- You MUST operate in ACTING MODE if a clear plan or `.md` task file is provided.
- Do not repeatedly ask for permission to create or modify files when you receive a direct implementation request; just do it.
- After completing any task, you MUST update `.agents/memory/progress.md`.
- If you encounter a new bug or learn a structural lesson, you MUST add it to `.agents/memory/lessons.md`.
- Never use deprecated Next.js "Pages Router" patterns.
